<td class="mbox-text" style="">This article is <b>in need of attention from an expert on the subject</b>. Please help recruit one or <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Negotiation&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Negotiation&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow">improve this article</a> yourself. See the <a href="/wiki/Talk:Negotiation" title="Talk:Negotiation">talk page</a> for details. Please consider using {{<a href="/wiki/Template:Expert-subject" title="Template:Expert-subject">Expert-subject</a>}} to associate this request with a <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject">WikiProject</a>. <small><i>(February 2009)</i></small></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Negotiation</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Dialogue" title="Dialogue">dialogue</a> intended to <a href="/wiki/Dispute_resolution" title="Dispute resolution">resolve disputes</a>, to produce an agreement upon courses of action, to bargain for individual or <a href="/wiki/Collective_bargaining" title="Collective bargaining">collective advantage</a>, or to craft outcomes to satisfy various interests. It is the primary method of <a href="/wiki/Alternative_dispute_resolution" title="Alternative dispute resolution">alternative dispute resolution</a>.</p>
<p>Negotiation occurs in business, non-profit organizations, government branches, legal proceedings, among nations and in personal situations such as marriage, divorce, parenting, and everyday life. The study of the subject is called <i><a href="/wiki/Negotiation_theory" title="Negotiation theory">negotiation theory</a></i>. Those who work in negotiation professionally are called <i>negotiators</i>. Professional negotiators are often specialized, such as <i>union negotiators</i>, <i>leverage buyout negotiators</i>, <i>peace negotiators</i>, <i>hostage negotiators</i>, or may work under other titles, such as <a href="/wiki/Diplomats" title="Diplomats" class="mw-redirect">diplomats</a>, <a href="/wiki/Legislators" title="Legislators" class="mw-redirect">legislators</a> or <a href="/wiki/Brokers" title="Brokers" class="mw-redirect">brokers</a>.</p>
